In a world where video now dominates everything, sometimes you forget to take a photo. Photos still say a thousand words. I went skinning today in -2 degrees. The whole trip was 4 miles long took just under 3 hours. Half way through the climb I went to post a video story and saw how goofy I looked in the middle of the struggle 😂 I didn’t take a photo at first and put my phone away. Walked 10 yards and decided I needed a photo of how dumb I look. Mainly because I know when I am going through old videos and photos this photo will tell me all thousand of the words I had going through my head while I was in my pain cave walking up 1,200 feet of vertical in under zero degree temperatures for a mid level snowboard run. 😂 What I am trying to say is take photos even if you don’t post them.
